questions.detailed_answer:
Part a:
Step 1: f(x) = 2e^{-2x} for x>0, starts at 2 when x=0, decreases to 0 as x→∞.
Step 2: Sketch shows asymptote at y=0.

Part b:
Step 1: Pr(X < 3) = ∫_0^3 2e^{-2x} dx = [-e^{-2x}]_0^3 = -e^{-6} - (-e^0) = 1 - e^{-6}
Step 2: Final answer: 1 - e^{-6}

Part c:
Step 1: Pr(X ≥ a) = ∫_a^∞ 2e^{-2x} dx = [ -e^{-2x} ]_a^∞ = 0 - (-e^{-2a}) = e^{-2a}
Step 2: Set e^{-2a} = e^{-2}, so -2a = -2, a=1
Step 3: Final answer: a = 1
